="2" column-width="proportional-column-width(1)"/><fo:table-column column-number="3" column-width="proportional-column-width(1)"/><fo:table-body><fo:table-row block-progression-dimension.minimum="14pt"><fo:table-cell text-align="start" display-align="after" relative-align="baseline"><fo:block><fo:block/></fo:block></fo:table-cell><fo:table-cell text-align="center" display-align="after" relative-align="baseline"><fo:block><fo:block/></fo:block></fo:table-cell><fo:table-cell text-align="end" display-align="after" relative-align="baseline"><fo:block><fo:block/></fo:block></fo:table-cell></fo:table-row></fo:table-body></fo:table></fo:block></fo:static-content><fo:static-content flow-name="xsl-region-after-blank"><fo:block font-family="Times New Roman, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" margin-left="0pt"><fo:table table-layout="fixed" width="100%" border-top-width="0.5pt" border-top-style="solid" border-top-color="black"><fo:table-column column-number="1" column-width="proportional-column-width(1)"/><fo:table-column column-number="2" column-width="proportional-column-width(1)"/><fo:table-column column-number="3" column-width="proportional-column-width(1)"/><fo:table-body><fo:table-row block-progression-dimension.minimum="14pt"><fo:table-cell text-align="start" display-align="after" relative-align="baseline"><fo:block><fo:block/></fo:block></fo:table-cell><fo:table-cell text-align="center" display-align="after" relative-align="baseline"><fo:block><fo:block/></fo:block></fo:table-cell><fo:table-cell text-align="end" display-align="after" relative-align="baseline"><fo:block><fo:block/></fo:block></fo:table-cell></fo:table-row></fo:table-body></fo:table></fo:block></fo:static-content><fo:flow flow-name="xsl-region-body"><fo:block id="d6e191"><fo:block><fo:block><fo:block text-align="center" font-size="24.8832pt" space-before="18.6624pt" font-weight="bold" font-family="Arial, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, sans-serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats"><fo:block keep-with-next.within-column="always" hyphenate="false">Part I. The People of the World</fo:block></fo:block><fo:block text-align="center" font-size="20.736pt" space-before="15.552pt" font-weight="bold" font-style="italic" font-family="Arial, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, sans-serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats">אומות העולם - Umot haOlam</fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block>
        <fo:block space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.maximum="1.2em"><fo:inline font-style="italic">Umot haOlam</fo:inline> is translated as "The People of the World". Now that
            we have a little bit of information on the substance of souls that emenate from
                <fo:inline font-style="italic">klipah</fo:inline>, we can now talk about a certain type of soul that the
                <fo:inline font-style="italic">Umot haOlam</fo:inline> have. <fo:inline font-style="italic">Umot haOlam</fo:inline> is the
                <fo:inline font-style="italic">ikkar</fo:inline> term for anyone who is not <fo:inline font-style="italic">bnei
                Yisrael</fo:inline> and are connected only to this world and do not have a portion in
                <fo:inline font-style="italic">Olam haBa</fo:inline>/The World to Come.<fo:footnote><fo:inline><fo:inline font-family="Times New Roman, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" font-size="75%" font-weight="normal" font-style="normal" baseline-shift="super">7</fo:inline></fo:inline><fo:footnote-body font-family="Times New Roman, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" font-size="8pt" font-weight="normal" font-style="normal" text-align="justify" start-indent="0pt" end-indent="0pt" text-indent="0pt" hyphenate="true" wrap-option="wrap" linefeed-treatment="treat-as-space">
                <fo:block><fo:inline font-family="Times New Roman, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" font-size="75%" font-weight="normal" font-style="normal" baseline-shift="super">7</fo:inline>Lessons in Tanya, Chapter 1</fo:block>
            </fo:footnote-body></fo:footnote>
            <fo:inline font-style="italic">Umot haOlam</fo:inline> are in contrast to <fo:inline font-style="italic">Chasidei Umot
                haOlam</fo:inline>. <fo:inline font-style="italic">Chasidei Umot haOlam</fo:inline> are not of
                <fo:inline font-style="italic">bnei Yisrael</fo:inline> in this domain, but <fo:inline font-weight="bold">are</fo:inline> connected to <fo:inline font-style="italic">Olam haBa</fo:inline>/The World to Come. Both
                <fo:inline font-style="italic">Chasidei Umot haOlam</fo:inline> and <fo:inline font-style="italic">Bnei Yisrael</fo:inline> have
                <fo:inline font-style="italic">nefashot behemot</fo:inline>/animal souls that emanate from the same place:
                <fo:inline font-style="italic">klipat nogah</fo:inline>, which is a mixture of pure and impure and such a
                <fo:inline font-style="italic">nefesh</fo:inline> can be elevated. <fo:inline font-style="italic">Klipat Nogah</fo:inline> is
            where all clean animals emanate from. A <fo:inline font-style="italic">nefesh</fo:inline>/soul from the
                <fo:inline font-style="italic">klipat tameyut</fo:inline> cannot yet be elevated; this is where all
            unclean animals emanate from and this is the soul type of <fo:inline font-style="italic">Umot
                haOlam</fo:inline>.</fo:block>
        <fo:block space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.maximum="1.2em">Every human being takes an oath in utero to be righteous.<fo:footnote><fo:inline><fo:inline font-family="Times New Roman, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" font-size="75%" font-weight="normal" font-style="normal" baseline-shift="super">8</fo:inline></fo:inline><fo:footnote-body font-family="Times New Roman, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" font-size="8pt" font-weight="normal" font-style="normal" text-align="justify" start-indent="0pt" end-indent="0pt" text-indent="0pt" hyphenate="true" wrap-option="wrap" linefeed-treatment="treat-as-space">
                <fo:block><fo:inline font-family="Times New Roman, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" font-size="75%" font-weight="normal" font-style="normal" baseline-shift="super">8</fo:inline>Niddah 30b, Iyov</fo:block>
            </fo:footnote-body></fo:footnote> The <fo:inline font-style="italic">Umot haOlam</fo:inline> have forsaken this oath. All human
            beings have 613 parts of the body.<fo:footnote><fo:inline><fo:inline font-family="Times New Roman, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" font-size="75%" font-weight="normal" font-style="normal" baseline-shift="super">9</fo:inline></fo:inline><fo:footnote-body font-family="Times New Roman, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" font-size="8pt" font-weight="normal" font-style="normal" text-align="justify" start-indent="0pt" end-indent="0pt" text-indent="0pt" hyphenate="true" wrap-option="wrap" linefeed-treatment="treat-as-space">
                <fo:block><fo:inline font-family="Times New Roman, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" font-size="75%" font-weight="normal" font-style="normal" baseline-shift="super">9</fo:inline>Tanya, Ari Kaplan Inner Space, Transforming the Inner Self, pg 38, ft
                    52</fo:block>
            </fo:footnote-body></fo:footnote>
            <fo:footnote><fo:inline><fo:inline font-family="Times New Roman, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" font-size="75%" font-weight="normal" font-style="normal" baseline-shift="super">10</fo:inline></fo:inline><fo:footnote-body font-family="Times New Roman, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" font-size="8pt" font-weight="normal" font-style="normal" text-align="justify" start-indent="0pt" end-indent="0pt" text-indent="0pt" hyphenate="true" wrap-option="wrap" linefeed-treatment="treat-as-space">
                <fo:block><fo:inline font-family="Times New Roman, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" font-size="75%" font-weight="normal" font-style="normal" baseline-shift="super">10</fo:inline>Likutei Torah, Eikev 13b; 14a</fo:block>
            </fo:footnote-body></fo:footnote> These 613 parts correlate to the 613 <fo:inline font-style="italic">mitzvot</fo:inline> written in
            the <fo:inline font-style="italic">Torah</fo:inline> and each have a respective conduit that connect to
                <fo:inline font-style="italic">haShem</fo:inline>. When you fulfill a <fo:inline font-style="italic">mitzvah</fo:inline>, you
            complete this conduit and Godliness flows into the world.<fo:footnote><fo:inline><fo:inline font-family="Times New Roman, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" font-size="75%" font-weight="normal" font-style="normal" baseline-shift="super">11</fo:inline></fo:inline><fo:footnote-body font-family="Times New Roman, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" font-size="8pt" font-weight="normal" font-style="normal" text-align="justify" start-indent="0pt" end-indent="0pt" text-indent="0pt" hyphenate="true" wrap-option="wrap" linefeed-treatment="treat-as-space">
                <fo:block><fo:inline font-family="Times New Roman, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" font-size="75%" font-weight="normal" font-style="normal" baseline-shift="super">11</fo:inline>Tanya, Iggeret haKodesh, 7</fo:block>
            </fo:footnote-body></fo:footnote></fo:block>
        <fo:block space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.maximum="1.2em">Of those 613 parts, 248 are bones that desire to do the positive
                <fo:inline font-style="italic">mitzvot</fo:inline>. All men are called to love
            <fo:inline font-style="italic">haShem</fo:inline>, whether they do so or not is up to them.<fo:footnote><fo:inline><fo:inline font-family="Times New Roman, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" font-size="75%" font-weight="normal" font-style="normal" baseline-shift="super">12</fo:inline></fo:inline><fo:footnote-body font-family="Times New Roman, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" font-size="8pt" font-weight="normal" font-style="normal" text-align="justify" start-indent="0pt" end-indent="0pt" text-indent="0pt" hyphenate="true" wrap-option="wrap" linefeed-treatment="treat-as-space">
                <fo:block><fo:inline font-family="Times New Roman, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" font-size="75%" font-weight="normal" font-style="normal" baseline-shift="super">12</fo:inline>Rambam, Book of Mitzvot, 3rd Principle(p.17 Touger)</fo:block>
            </fo:footnote-body></fo:footnote></fo:block>
        <fo:block space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.maximum="1.2em">The <fo:inline font-style="italic">Umot haOlam</fo:inline> forsake the desire to love
                <fo:inline font-style="italic">haShem</fo:inline> and are motivated only for self-serving motives. Even if
            someone from the <fo:inline font-style="italic">Umot haOlam</fo:inline> do an act of kindness, it is only to
            fulfill a selfish desire to do kindness and is not true kindness.</fo:block>
        <fo:block space-before.minimum="0.5em" space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.maximum="2em" space-after.minimum="0.5em" space-after.optimum="1em" space-after.maximum="2em" keep-together.within-column="always" border-style="solid" border-width="1pt" border-color="black" background-color="#DDDDDD" padding-start="12pt" padding-end="12pt" padding-top="6pt" padding-bottom="6pt" margin-left="0pt" margin-right="0pt" id="d6e243"><fo:block/><fo:block space-before.optimum="0pt" space-before.minimum="0pt" space-before.maximum="0pt">R"AMBAM writes: Every human being who's spirit moves them, can obtain understanding, and with
                his knowledge, set himself different and stand before <fo:inline font-style="italic">haShem</fo:inline>,
                to serve and minister to Him and to know <fo:inline font-style="italic">haShem</fo:inline>, walking
                straight as <fo:inline font-style="italic">Elokim</fo:inline> made him, and can remove the yoke of the
                thoughts of <fo:inline font-style="italic">bnei Adam</fo:inline>. This human being is sanctified like the
                    <fo:inline font-style="italic">Kadosh Kadoshim</fo:inline>. <fo:inline font-style="italic">haShem</fo:inline> is his portion
                and heritage forever and will provide what is sufficient for him in this world like
                He provides for priests and Levites. Thus David, peace be upon him, said
                    "<fo:inline font-style="italic">haShem</fo:inline> is my lot and my portion; You are my cup; you
                support my lot."<fo:footnote><fo:inline><fo:inline font-family="Times New Roman, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" font-size="75%" font-weight="normal" font-style="normal" baseline-shift="super">13</fo:inline></fo:inline><fo:footnote-body font-family="Times New Roman, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" font-size="8pt" font-weight="normal" font-style="normal" text-align="justify" start-indent="0pt" end-indent="0pt" text-indent="0pt" hyphenate="true" wrap-option="wrap" linefeed-treatment="treat-as-space">
                    <fo:block><fo:inline font-family="Times New Roman, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" font-size="75%" font-weight="normal" font-style="normal" baseline-shift="super">13</fo:inline>Tehillim 16:5</fo:block>
                </fo:footnote-body></fo:footnote>
                <fo:footnote><fo:inline><fo:inline font-family="Times New Roman, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" font-size="75%" font-weight="normal" font-style="normal" baseline-shift="super">14</fo:inline></fo:inline><fo:footnote-body font-family="Times New Roman, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" font-size="8pt" font-weight="normal" font-style="normal" text-align="justify" start-indent="0pt" end-indent="0pt" text-indent="0pt" hyphenate="true" wrap-option="wrap" linefeed-treatment="treat-as-space">
                    <fo:block><fo:inline font-family="Times New Roman, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" font-size="75%" font-weight="normal" font-style="normal" baseline-shift="super">14</fo:inline>Rambam, Mishneh Torah, Hilchot Shemita v'Yovel 13:13</fo:block>
