 font-family="Arial, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, sans-serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats"><fo:block margin-left="0pt"><fo:block font-size="24.8832pt" font-weight="bold"><fo:block keep-with-next.within-column="always" space-before.optimum="10pt" space-before.minimum="10pt * 0.8" space-before.maximum="10pt * 1.2" hyphenate="false" text-align="start" start-indent="0pt" hyphenation-character="-" hyphenation-push-character-count="2" hyphenation-remain-character-count="2">Chapter 9. Sojourners of Lions</fo:block></fo:block><fo:block space-before="0.5em" font-style="italic" font-size="14.4pt" font-weight="bold">גרי - Gerei Ari'ot</fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block>
	
	
	<fo:block space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.maximum="1.2em"><fo:inline font-style="italic">Gerei Ari'ot</fo:inline> are sojourners of lions. This is a term for sojourners who
		were so fearful of the wildlife in the area, they took upon the <fo:inline font-style="italic">Torah</fo:inline>,
		thinking the <fo:inline font-style="italic">Torah</fo:inline> would protect them. They had no intention of keeping
		the <fo:inline font-style="italic">Torah</fo:inline> for its own sake, for the sake of Heaven, or the like.<fo:footnote><fo:inline><fo:inline font-family="Times New Roman, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" font-size="75%" font-weight="normal" font-style="normal" baseline-shift="super">1</fo:inline></fo:inline><fo:footnote-body font-family="Times New Roman, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" font-size="8pt" font-weight="normal" font-style="normal" text-align="justify" start-indent="0pt" end-indent="0pt" text-indent="0pt" hyphenate="true" wrap-option="wrap" linefeed-treatment="treat-as-space"><fo:block><fo:inline font-family="Times New Roman, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" font-size="75%" font-weight="normal" font-style="normal" baseline-shift="super">1</fo:inline>II Kings I believe. The kuthim/Samaritans</fo:block></fo:footnote-body></fo:footnote></fo:block>
	<fo:block space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.maximum="1.2em">The term <fo:inline font-style="italic">goy</fo:inline> seems to have a neutral connotation, where any
		negativity toward <fo:inline font-style="italic">goy</fo:inline> would be implied. However, it seems during the
		time of the Prophets and Writings, <fo:inline font-style="italic">goyim</fo:inline> started getting a bad wrap for
		being idol worshippers.</fo:block>
	<fo:block space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.maximum="1.2em">The etymology of the word from the etymological dictionary</fo:block>
