lock font-family="Arial, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, sans-serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats"><fo:block margin-left="0pt"><fo:block font-size="24.8832pt" font-weight="bold"><fo:block keep-with-next.within-column="always" space-before.optimum="10pt" space-before.minimum="10pt * 0.8" space-before.maximum="10pt * 1.2" hyphenate="false" text-align="start" start-indent="0pt" hyphenation-character="-" hyphenation-push-character-count="2" hyphenation-remain-character-count="2">Chapter 10. Calculating Converts</fo:block></fo:block><fo:block space-before="0.5em" font-style="italic" font-size="14.4pt" font-weight="bold">גרים גרורים - Gerim Gerurim</fo:block></fo:block></fo:block></fo:block>
	
	
	<fo:block space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.maximum="1.2em">Element of selfish gain for only their animal soul. As opposed to an element of fear of
		losing the life of one's animal soul like <fo:inline font-style="italic">gerim ariyot</fo:inline> from a previous
		chapter.</fo:block>
	<fo:block space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.maximum="1.2em"><fo:inline font-style="italic">Gerim of Mordecai and Esther</fo:inline> are most likely <fo:inline font-style="italic">Gerim
			Gerurim</fo:inline>.</fo:block>
	<fo:block space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.maximum="1.2em">The etymology of the word from the etymological dictionary - gerar means to chew cud. A pig
		doesn't gerar. See conversation with Jake Fry.</fo:block>
	<fo:block space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.maximum="1.2em"><fo:inline font-style="italic">Gerim Gerurim</fo:inline> come for selfish motives and attach to
			<fo:inline font-style="italic">Yisrael</fo:inline> when the hand of <fo:inline font-style="italic">Yisrael</fo:inline> is strong.
		This is explained in <fo:inline font-style="italic">Avodah Zarah</fo:inline> 2b which is before the war of
			<fo:inline font-style="italic">Gog u'Magog</fo:inline>. During the war, these <fo:inline font-style="italic">gerim
			gerurim</fo:inline> will break the <fo:inline font-style="italic">mitzvot</fo:inline> they were keeping and
		cast them away. There will be a remnant of these gerim, however, that will still keep the
			<fo:inline font-style="italic">mitzvot</fo:inline> and <fo:inline font-style="italic">haShem</fo:inline> will make them and their
		language pure and all will call upon the name of haShem and serve him in oneness. This is
		explained in <fo:inline font-style="italic">Berakhot</fo:inline> 57a and the commentary on
			<fo:inline font-style="italic">Zephaniah</fo:inline> 3:9 by <fo:inline font-style="italic">RADAK</fo:inline> which shows the
			<fo:inline font-style="italic">goyim</fo:inline> returning to <fo:inline font-style="italic">haShem</fo:inline> and becoming
			<fo:inline font-style="italic">gerim</fo:inline>.<fo:footnote><fo:inline><fo:inline font-family="Times New Roman, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" font-size="75%" font-weight="normal" font-style="normal" baseline-shift="super">1</fo:inline></fo:inline><fo:footnote-body font-family="Times New Roman, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" font-size="8pt" font-weight="normal" font-style="normal" text-align="justify" start-indent="0pt" end-indent="0pt" text-indent="0pt" hyphenate="true" wrap-option="wrap" linefeed-treatment="treat-as-space">
			<fo:block><fo:inline font-family="Times New Roman, Arial Unicode MS, Tahoma, Batang, serif,Symbol,ZapfDingbats" font-size="75%" font-weight="normal" font-style="normal" baseline-shift="super">1</fo:inline>The people who will remain after the war of Gog in their first language will make
				it clear to them that they will not utter another God in their language, but all
				will call in the name of the Lord. This is a clear language as he said in the
				prophecy of Zechariah on that day there will be one God and His name is one. Will
				turn into worshiping God alone in a clear language is the language of holiness in
				which alone is called the honorable name - <fo:inline font-style="italic">RADAK</fo:inline> on
					<fo:inline font-style="italic">Zephaniah</fo:inline> 3:9</fo:block>
			<fo:block space-before.optimum="1em" space-before.minimum="0.8em" space-before.maximum="1.2em">פי' העמים שישארו אחר מלחמת גוג שפתם הראשונה אהפוך אותה עליהם בשפה ברורה שלא יוציאו
				בשפתם אלהים אחרים אלא כולם יקראו בשם ה' זהו שפה ברורה כמו שאמר בנבואת זכריה ביום
				ההוא יהיה ה' אחד ושמו אחד, והחכם רבי אברהם אבן עזרא ז"ל פירש יתהפכו לעבוד ה' לבדו
				בשפה ברורה היא לשון הקדש שבה לבדה נקרא השם הנכבד:</fo:block>
		</fo:footnote-body></fo:footnote></fo:block>
</fo:flow></fo:page-sequence>

